TASK_DESCRIPTION=Large audit-driven cleanup. Full audit attached as audit.md. User wants parallel execution. See attachment for findings.

CRITICAL CONTEXT:
- Audit itself is stale in places: refs Manager/SM/doey-manager.md. Current system: Taskmaster/Subtaskmaster (renamed task #96).
- watchdog-scan.sh, watchdog-wait.sh ALREADY marked DEPRECATED in current CLAUDE.md
- on-notification.sh, taskmaster-wait.sh ALREADY in current CLAUDE.md hook table
- Task 550 (tui/ popup fix) JUST SHIPPED — no more tui/ conflicts expected, but coordinate anyway

PHASED EXECUTION (Taskmaster autonomous):

Phase 1 — single worker, read-only validation:
Go through audit.md line by line, grep/read HEAD, mark each finding STILL_REAL/ALREADY_FIXED/PARTIALLY_REAL/WRONG. Output: validation-report.md in attachments.

Phase 2 — parallel fan-out, one worker per disjoint cluster, only for STILL_REAL findings:
A. Real bugs: stop-status.sh BUSY guard, watchdog-scan.sh pane ID (if exists), on-pre-tool-use.sh info panel fallthrough
B. doey.sh: watchdog ghost, dead funcs, help text, doey doctor pwd, /tmp mktemp, info-panel.sh PATH
C. CLAUDE.md: tables (architecture/tools/hooks/testing), line count
D. Config: doey-config-default.sh, settings-panel.sh, pane-border-status.sh
E. Agents: surviving stale .md (after rename check)
F. common.sh: is_watchdog/notify_watchdog cleanup
G. Skills: doey-debug, doey-add-window, doey-add-team, doey-repair, doey-watchdog-compact rename, doey-kill-all-sessions trash, root SKILL.md dup
H. Docs: context-reference, debug-mode-design, test-worktree, linux-server

Phase 3 — integration:
go build tui/... PASS, tests/test-bash-compat.sh PASS, doey doctor PASS, one commit per cluster, push.

Rules:
- No cross-cluster file edits
- Skip clusters with zero still-real findings
- NEVER touch tui/ (safety habit from 550)
- Phase 2 launches autonomously after Phase 1, no Boss check-in
- Summary report to Boss at Phase 3 completion
